`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- The `DispatchContext` interface acts as a **discriminated context object** — instead of function overloads or optional positional args, all inputs arrive in one bag. This keeps the call site clean and makes it easy to add new actions without changing the signature.
- Mocking `GameActions` at the module level in tests keeps the dispatcher tests **pure routing tests** — they never touch the ECS world or game store, making them fast and isolated. This is the cleanest way to test dispatch tables in this codebase.
